# 5. 優しい帰り道

Teacher: Alright, you're all free to go. Please get home safe, everyone.
Classmates: *Sigh* They assigned us way too much homework today.
Classmates: I know, right? I'm thinking about ditching club...
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: (I need to tell Dad the next time he comes over...)
Mafuyu: (About what happened that night...)
Mafuyu: (He's waiting for me to tell him. He's waiting for me to come home.)
Mafuyu: (But...)
Mafuyu: ...
Classmates: Do you have club today, Mafuyu? I forget. If not, wanna work on these homework assignments together?
Classmates: I know what you're up to. You just want to copy her answers!
Classmates: Huh? N-No, I dunno what you're talking about...
Mafuyu: Oh, that's naughty. It's important that you do your own homework.
Classmates: Yeah, I know! But let's still do these together! I'll make sure that my eyes don't wander!
Mafuyu: Hmm... Then...
Mafuyu: Oh...
Mafuyu: (A message? From who..?)
Mizuki: Hey, Mafuyu! Had a busy day?
Mafuyu: What are you doing here...?
Mizuki: I figured it was about time for your school to get out. So, I thought we could walk home together.
Mafuyu: But you don't go to this school...
Mizuki: C'mon, who cares about the details?
Mizuki: So, how about it? Wanna walk with me?
Mafuyu: You came all this way, so I suppose it'd be rude to say no...
Mizuki: Haha. You're always so nice. Anyway, let's go!
Mizuki: So, I decided to make some ribbons out of the rolls of fabric I bought at that shop for Rin and the others! And they turned out really cute!
Mafuyu: Really?
Mizuki: Yeah! I wanna make you one too, so let me know which fabric you'd like me to use! They're honestly all really adorable♪
Mafuyu: You can choose since I probably won't have much of an opinion.
Mizuki: Alright, in that case, you and Miku are gonna have a matching pair. I'm sure she'll really like that!
Mizuki: I'll let you know when I've drawn my design, so stay tuned♪
Mafuyu: Okay.
Mizuki: Come to think of it, you took a day off from working yesterday. How are you feeling? Better...?
Mafuyu: *Nod* I feel much more at ease now...
Mizuki: Really? That's good to hear...
Mizuki: (But you don't just get over something like this...)
Mizuki: Sorry. The thing is, Miku and the others told me about why you took yesterday off...
Mizuki: You want to tell your dad about what happened that night, but you're afraid to, right...?
Mafuyu: Oh...
Mafuyu: You came all this way to ask me that...?
Mizuki: Yeah. I know I'm being pretty nosy, but I wanted to talk to you about it...
Mizuki: Are you still afraid...?
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: Yes...
Mafuyu: I want to tell him about what happened that night. I want to tell him how I really feel...
Mafuyu: But...
Mizuki: I know...
Mizuki: You're afraid that he won't understand...
Mizuki: Especially since he's someone really important to you.
Mizuki: The thought of possibly being rejected after telling him everything is just so terrifying...
Mizuki: Which makes you think, why bother telling him at all?
Mafuyu: ...
Mizuki: That's probably why I became stuck for so long too.
Mizuki: But I'm starting to think that...
Mizuki: There are more people who will accept me for who I am than I realized.
Mafuyu: What...?
Mizuki: Now, I have a feeling that there'll be more people that'll say, “Thanks for telling me,” and, “No matter what, I'm on your side,” after breaking some big news to them...
Mizuki: That's how I feel now...
Mafuyu: ...
Mizuki: I know you're scared. Shaking that fear off isn't easy.
Mizuki: But...
Mizuki: If you believe that there is even the slightest chance that your dad will understand... Then I think you two should talk...
Mafuyu: I...
Mizuki: Ack, it's starting to rain! Talk about bad timing...
Mizuki: I didn't bring an umbrella, so let's head home before we get drenched...!
Mizuki: You're that way, right, Mafuyu? Will you be okay on your own?
Mafuyu: *Nod*
Mafuyu: Mizuki...
Mizuki: Hm?
Mafuyu: Thank you...
Mizuki: Haha. No problem.
Mizuki: Anyway, see you on Nightcord!
Mizuki: (I'm such a hypocrite...)
Mizuki: (I told Mafuyu to do the very thing that I can't...)
Mizuki: (But...)
Mizuki: On my side, huh...?
